cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR 

The paper deals with pose estimation, tracking, and action recognition of articulated objects from depth images, which are all related to computer vision (cs.CV). The use of Lie group theory is a mathematical framework that is commonly used in robotics (cs.RO) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also mentions the use of convolutional neural networks (cs.AI) and regression forest methods, which are common machine learning techniques. Finally, the paper evaluates its approach on lab animals and human hand, which falls under the category of graphics (cs.GR).
